en_144267_0	A tax evasion amnesty in India has prompted tens of thousands of people to declare more than $9.5bn in undeclared income and assets.
en_144267_1	Finance minister Arun Jaitley said the four-month window that ended on Friday brought in 64,275 declarations.
en_144267_2	All were offered immunity from prosecution in return for paying tax, a surcharge and a penalty.
en_144267_3	It is estimated that the government could raise nearly $4.5bn from the scheme.
en_144267_4	Undeclared income or "black money" is a huge issue in India.
